Friday                                     11:59:15                           10:14:53
Saturday                                 12:01:30                           10:15:24
Sunday                                   12:01:19                           10:15:11
If you are doing an experiment that requires precision time interval measurements, which of the two clocks will you prefer ?", "fibs": ["noon"]}
{"text": "Answer   The range of variation over the seven days of observations is 162 s for clock 1, and 31 s for clock 2.", "fibs": ["Answer"]}
{"text": "The average reading of clock 1 is much closer to the standard time than the average reading of clock 2.", "fibs": ["reading"]}
{"text": "The important point is that a clock’s zero error is not as significant for precision work as its variation, because a ‘zero-error’ can always be easily corrected.", "fibs": ["point"]}
{"text": "Hence clock 2 is to be preferred to clock 1.", "fibs": ["clock"]}
{"text": "Example 2.7  We measure the period of oscillation of a simple pendulum.", "fibs": ["Example"]}
