2.6.2  Combination of Errors
If we do an experiment involving several measurements, we must know how the errors in all the measurements combine.", "fibs": ["example"]}
{"text": "For example, mass density is obtained by deviding mass by the volume of the substance.", "fibs": ["example"]}
{"text": "If we have errors in the measurement of mass and of the sizes or dimensions, we must know what the error will be in the density of the substance.", "fibs": ["measurement"]}
{"text": "For this, we use the following procedure.", "fibs": ["use"]}
{"text": "How will you measure the length of a line?", "fibs": ["measure"]}
{"text": "What a naïve question, at this stage, you might say!", "fibs": ["naïve"]}
{"text": "But what if it is not a straight line?", "fibs": ["line"]}
{"text": "Draw a zigzag line in your copy, or on the blackboard.", "fibs": ["zigzag"]}
{"text": "You might take a thread, place it along the line, open up the thread, and measure its length.", "fibs": ["thread"]}
{"text": "Now imagine that you want to measure the length of a national highway, a river, the railway track between two stations, or the boundary between two states or two nations.", "fibs": ["measure"]}
{"text": "If you take a string of length 1 metre or 100 metre, keep it along the line, shift its position every time, the arithmetic of man-hours of labour and expenses on the project is not commensurate with the outcome.", "fibs": ["string"]}
{"text": "Moreover, errors are bound to occur in this enormous task.", "fibs": ["task"]}
{"text": "There is an interesting fact about this.", "fibs": ["fact"]}
{"text": "France and Belgium share a common international boundary, whose length mentioned in the official documents of the two countries differs substantially!", "fibs": ["share"]}
{"text": "Go one step beyond and imagine the coastline where land meets sea.", "fibs": ["step"]}
{"text": "Roads and rivers have fairly mild bends as compared to a coastline.", "fibs": ["coastline"]}
{"text": "Even so, all documents, including our school books, contain information on the length of the coastline of Gujarat or Andhra Pradesh, or the common boundary between two states, etc.", "fibs": ["school"]}
{"text": "Railway tickets come with the distance between stations printed on them.", "fibs": ["distance"]}
{"text": "We have ‘milestones’ all along the roads indicating the distances to various towns.", "fibs": ["‘"]}
{"text": "One has to decide how much error one can tolerate and optimise cost-effectiveness.", "fibs": ["error"]}
{"text": "If you want smaller errors, it will involve high technology and high costs.", "fibs": ["technology"]}
{"text": "Suffice it to say that it requires fairly advanced level of physics, mathematics, engineering and technology.", "fibs": ["level"]}
{"text": "It belongs to the areas of fractals, which has lately become popular in theoretical physics.", "fibs": ["physics"]}
{"text": "Even then one doesn’t know how much to rely on the figure that props up, as is clear from the story of France and Belgium.", "fibs": ["doesn"]}
{"text": "Incidentally, this story of the France-Belgium discrepancy appears on the first page of an advanced Physics book on the subject of fractals and chaos!", "fibs": ["story"]}
{"text": "(a)  Error of a sum or a difference
