The maximum value of the error ∆Z  is again  ∆A + ∆B.", "fibs": ["error"]}
{"text": "Hence the rule : When two quantities are added or subtracted, the absolute error in the final result is the sum of the absolute errors in the individual quantities.", "fibs": ["rule"]}
